00:04:05.596 --> 00:04:06.096
Anyone?

00:04:06.096 --> 00:04:08.660
Great, so that's
pretty much everyone.

00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:11.990
So for myself, I come
from a background where

00:04:11.990 --> 00:04:15.590
basically I trained in
science and biochemistry

00:04:15.590 --> 00:04:18.821
and then went on to medicine
and then became a psychiatrist

00:04:18.821 --> 00:04:20.779
after training initially
in pediatrics and then

00:04:20.779 --> 00:04:24.420
adult psychiatry, became a child
and adolescent psychiatrist.

00:04:24.420 --> 00:04:27.270
And then when I was
trained in research,

00:04:27.270 --> 00:04:30.380
I was really beginning
at the period which

00:04:30.380 --> 00:04:34.180
was called the decade
of the brain, 1990.

00:04:34.180 --> 00:04:36.210
And so it became an
incredible opportunity

00:04:36.210 --> 00:04:38.580
to actually take the
science of the brain

00:04:38.580 --> 00:04:43.830
and try to apply it to practical
clinical use in psychiatry.

00:04:43.830 --> 00:04:46.850
And so I worked to help
create a field called

00:04:46.850 --> 00:04:48.900
interpersonal neurobiology.

00:04:48.900 --> 00:04:51.510
And that field basically takes
all the different disciplines

00:04:51.510 --> 00:04:55.760
of science and puts them
together into one framework.

00:04:55.760 --> 00:04:58.470
And so we have now 36
textbooks that I've

00:04:58.470 --> 00:05:00.440
